reviews.review_text: X The boys are on fire and mr Miller got it right like usual. If a show has 50 five star reviews and the Charlie  Miller remaster has none I'll grab it every time. Deadheads check out Ekoostik Hookah. They are a really talented jam band. Start with 6-30-07, 10-19-07 and 3-28-08. A little tip from your uncle Lar. I'm here to help ya kids.
Once Again Thank you Charlie for the vibes !!!!

Best source Beats Ashley source which I often prefer.  Much more separation and clarity here.  

Killer show dripping from start to finish.  A true 5*, and Mr. Miller puts the icing on the cake with this re-master.  

Summer '84 - look forward to dialing it in with the time blender on the other side.

You know it's gonna get stranger...so let's get on with the show Nice crisp sound here!~ I can't believe that I have not rated this one yet..for it is one of my favorites of the year!! I can't say a dream set but I'll say it's a barn burner from start to finish..I always like the way Stranger sets the pace and yeah it's a Bobby tune! It use to kill me how so many people were negative towards Bobby..The universe brought all these guys together to play!! Jerry wasn't the only member of the band~~? I said my peace...I'm not going to talk about every tune,but in the 2nd set it just flows with passionate heat!!! I find myself grabbing this out of my CD booklet a lot..so please give it a whirl..Forever Grateful>Forever Dead!!!!!!!!!
Sign Me Up I'd pay $975 to see this today.

Not Bad The band might have been feeling a little tired from the KC show.
Highlights:  Feel Like A Stranger, He's Gone

My First Show I was 22. Grew up in Cedar Rapids. Asked all my friends to go with me. Went alone. Say no more I was hooked. Great show, stoopid police. Fives Seasons not known for acoustics. This mix is sweet. Thanks Charlie! Great set!
